From: pocknix <noreply@pocknix>
Subject: [PATCH] tu/msm: drop redundant per-submit VM_BIND wait/signal fences

Turnip on the msm VM_BIND path adds an extra wait + extra signal syncobj
timepoint to every graphics-queue submit to order memory-bind ops against
rendering. That ordering is already guaranteed by the fences set up elsewhere
in the submit path, so these two are pure overhead — a redundant sync round-trip
on the hot path of every frame. On a vblank-locked, minimally-buffered compositor
(gamescope) doing multiple composite submits per frame, that tax is paid many
times per 16ms and isn't hidden by buffering.

Source: armada-packages / batocera-linux (0001-fix-freedreno-vulkan / "#14656
VM_BIND fix"). Verbatim.

diff --git a/src/freedreno/vulkan/tu_knl_drm_msm.cc b/src/freedreno/vulkan/tu_knl_drm_msm.cc
index e3a6916..d60db42 100644
--- a/src/freedreno/vulkan/tu_knl_drm_msm.cc
+++ b/src/freedreno/vulkan/tu_knl_drm_msm.cc
@@ -1257,11 +1257,8 @@ msm_queue_submit(struct tu_queue *queue, void *_submit,
    uint64_t other_timepoint =
       submit->binds.size != 0 ? queue->gfx_timepoint :
       queue->sparse_timepoint;
-   uint32_t extra_wait_count =
-      (queue->type == TU_QUEUE_GFX && other_timepoint != 0) ? 1 : 0;
-   uint32_t extra_signal_count =
-      (queue->type == TU_QUEUE_GFX && has_vm_bind) ? 1 : 0;
-
+   uint32_t extra_wait_count = 0;
+   uint32_t extra_signal_count = 0;
    /* Allocate without wait timeline semaphores */
    in_syncobjs = (struct drm_msm_syncobj *) vk_zalloc(
       &queue->device->vk.alloc,
